'''caul'''
#The thin [[membrane]] which covers the lower [[intestines]].
#Part of the [[amniotic sac]] which sometimes [[shroud]]s a baby's head at birth.
#A membrane covering the face of certain children at birth, also called the [[veil]]. The phenomenon is often described as "being born behind the Veil." Not the commonly misunderstood remnant of the amniotic sac (see [[caulbearer]]).
#A style of close-fitting circular [[cap]] worn by women in the [[16th century]] and later, often made of [[linen]]. [http://www.elizabethancostume.net/headwear/caulmake.html]

